{"type":null,"faqId":15566,"title":"What can I do if the Y536A1 phone screen does not rotate automatically?","answer":"<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 113.45pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 113.45pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Turn\non the auto-rotate screen function.</span></p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char;'><span>Open the\nnotification panel and touch <img style=\"width: 15pt; height: 18.75pt;\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20141023045806700001.png\"><span>&nbsp;</span>to turn on the auto-rotate screen\nfunction. </span></p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 113.45pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 113.45pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>If\nthis happens when you are using a third-party application, check whether the\napplication is tilt sensor-based. </span></p>\n<p>\n<span style='font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt;'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Your phone's tilt sensor\nmay fail to work if certain system files are deleted. Back up </span></p>\n<p><span style='font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt;'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; important data\nand restore your phone to its factory settings or update your phone.</span>\n</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"7965","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1414011543000,"seriesProductName":"Y536-A1","visitedTimes":15,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Y536A1,screen,rotate","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}